body:
@aidan-plenert-macdonald — FWIW, we just added [initial read/write support for Cloud Bigtable][tf-bigtable] in [TF 1.10.0][tf-1.10], and you can store protocol buffers in Cloud Bigtable columns — in fact, you can store arbitrary bytes in Cloud Bigtable, since it doesn't enforce a typed schema. Hope this helps!

[tf-bigtable]: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/tree/master/tensorflow/contrib/bigtable
[tf-1.10]: https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/releases/tag/v1.10.0
